description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit highly motivated and enthusiastic clinical support workers (CSW). You will have excellent organisation and communication skills to complement our current out of hours service to provide 24/7 cover. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be working within the Hospital @ Night team supporting with Cannulation, Phlebotomy and ECG recording. In addition you will be supporting the medical and nursing teams in responding to acutely unwell patients.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are a committed individual who strives to provide excellent patient focused care and able to rise to new challenges then we would like to hear from you.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This position is working across various shifts (not inclusive of educational needs). Including: working weekend/bank holiday days, night shifts and weekdays. The H@N service operates a variety of shifts as above and you are strongly urged to consider your suitability to meet the service requirements prior to applying for this post.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Department has operational responsibility for Hospital @ Night across the organisation. As such, the post holder will be required to rotate between all campuses that make up Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have approval from your line manager to be released on secondment to proceed with this application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAdam Shelton-JohnsonJob titleLead NurseEmail addressAdam.shelton-johnson@nuh.nhs.ukTelephone number07812275450Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
